			<div class="content" id="post-content-2460604">
									

<p>I like it. The anomaly itself is unfortunately quite skimpy as far as narrative detail goes, but I especially like that a software glitch capable of altering the physical world and producing dangerous memes is just being used to spam ads.</p>
<p>I also get the impression that this P-labs successor actually got their shit together after taking a tighter focus, which is nice. On the downside, similar to the anomaly, it's not entirely clear what anomalous services they offer besides &quot;we can do IT security against anomalous things.&quot; If they stick around, I'd like to see what kind of paratech they bring to the table.</p>
<p>+1 in any case</p>

							</div>

								
					
